  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. The equation of a circle in the <em>x</em><em>y</em>-plane can be written as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus k right parenthesis squared equals r squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2212</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>\u2212</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where the center of the circle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis h comma k right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and the radius of the circle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math>. It\u2019s given that this circle has a center at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 19 comma 18 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and a radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 k\"><mn>9</mn><mi>k</mi></math>. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"19\"><mn>19</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"18\"><mn>18</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 k\"><mn>9</mn><mi>k</mi></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus k right parenthesis squared equals r squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><m